==English==
[[File:Zaanse mayonaise.jpg|thumb|Mayonnaise]]

===Etymology===
Borrowed from {{bor|en|fr|mayonnaise}}, possibly named after the city [[Maó]] ([[Mahón]] in Spanish), [[Minorca]], whence the recipe was brought back to France. Compare {{cog|es|mahonesa}}. Alternative suggested origins include the city of [[Bayonne]] ({{m|fr|bayonnaise}}); the French word {{m|fr|manier||to handle}}; the {{der|en|fro|moyeu||egg yolk}}; and the Duke of {{w|Mayenne}}.

